IMPRESSION: 
1. Numerous peripheral nerve sheath tumors in the head, neck, and upper 
chest, compatible with history of schwannomatosis, as described.  
Findings in the chest are unchanged since 11/29/12.
2. Masses in the left maxilla, retromaxillary trigone, and left 
supraglottic larynx as described, also likely peripheral nerve sheath 
tumors.
